# Aegis Gateway — Tor transparent-proxy configuration (spec §5; Etap 1).
#
# The gateway captures ALL DNS and TCP from the isolated Browser network and
# routes it through Tor. There is no SOCKS listener exposed to the browser: the
# browser sees a plain router, and the firewall transparently redirects its
# traffic to the ports below. UDP other than DNS is dropped by nftables (Tor
# cannot carry arbitrary UDP), which enforces the "no direct UDP" rule (spec §5).
#
# Port choices MUST match aegis_core::gateway::FirewallPolicy::fail_closed and the
# nftables ruleset:
#   DNSPort   = 5353   (firewall redirects downstream :53 udp/tcp here)
#   TransPort = 9040   (firewall redirects downstream tcp here)
#   ControlPort = 9051 (loopback only; used by aegis-healthcheck for bootstrap %)

DataDirectory /var/lib/tor
User debian-tor

# --- Transparent proxy listeners (bound to the downstream gateway address) ----
# 10.152.152.1 is the gateway's downstream address (matches GatewayConfig
# downstream_cidr 10.152.152.0/24). Binding here, never to the upstream NIC,
# means these listeners are only reachable from the isolated Browser network.
TransPort 10.152.152.1:9040
DNSPort   10.152.152.1:5353

# --- DNS automapping for .onion and general name resolution -------------------
# Give resolved names virtual IPs inside a private range the firewall pins to
# Tor, so the browser's connections to those IPs are transparently torified.
AutomapHostsOnResolve 1
AutomapHostsSuffixes .onion,.exit
VirtualAddrNetworkIPv4 10.192.0.0/10

# --- Control port for health probing (loopback only, cookie auth) -------------
ControlPort 127.0.0.1:9051
CookieAuthentication 1
CookieAuthFile /run/tor/control.authcookie
CookieAuthFileGroupReadable 1

# --- Hardening / no exit relaying; client only --------------------------------
SocksPort 0
ClientOnly 1
ExitRelay 0
AvoidDiskWrites 1
# Do not resolve or accept IPv6 upstream unless explicitly enabled; the firewall
# blocks IPv6 downstream regardless (spec §5 IPv6 leak prevention).
ClientUseIPv6 0
ClientPreferIPv6ORPort 0

# --- Bridges / pluggable transports (populated by the manager when configured)-
# The manager rewrites the block below via gateway-controller when TorConfig
# requests bridges. Left empty by default (direct Tor).
# UseBridges 1
# ClientTransportPlugin obfs4 exec /usr/bin/obfs4proxy
# Bridge obfs4 <ip:port> <fingerprint> cert=<...> iat-mode=0

# --- Logging: no client traffic logged; notices only, to the journal ----------
Log notice syslog
SafeLogging 1
